Do you idiots even know what "executive" producer means?it means that person had done ZERO work on the film,otherwise they would have received the normal "producer"title.Executive producer is a credit used to say thanks to a person that helped a film financially or by just adding their name to the cast to attract more financing or to promote the film.Very often even actors playing in the film receive this title,for various reasons,like attracting others actors to the cast,or taking a pay cut just because the budget couldn't afford their normal fee.
